DOCUMENT();
############################################################ # Load Macros ############################################################ loadMacros( "PGstandard.pl", "PGML.pl", "AnswerFormatHelp.pl", "PCCmacros.pl", "contextCurrency.pl", "contextPercent.pl", "parserLinearRelation.pl", "PGcourse.pl", ); COMMENT('Authored in PreTeXt');
############################################################ # Header ############################################################ TEXT(beginproblem());
############################################################ # PG Setup Code ############################################################ Context("Currency")->flags->set(trimTrailingZeros => 1); $final = 1400 + random(-300, 300, 10); $current = Currency($final); Context("Percent"); $decimal = random(0.01,0.03,0.001); $percent = Percent($decimal); Context("LinearRelation")->variables->are(r => 'Real'); $equation = LinearRelation("r + $decimal r = $final");
############################################################ # Body ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML Read the scenario. Then write a complete sentence that defines a variable to use. Lastly, write an equation to model the scenario. There is no need to solve the equation.
One year, the median rent for a one-bedroom apartment in a city was reported to be [`[$current]\text{.}`] This was reported to be an increase of [`[$percent]`] over the previous year. Based on this reporting, what was the median rent for of a one-bedroom apartment the previous year? Set up an equation to answer this question. There is no need to solve it.
[@KeyboardInstructions('Use [|r|]* as the variable.')@]**
[_]{$equation}{20}
END_PGML
